Chapter 7: Conclusion

7.1 Summary of Contributions

This dissertation has:

· Established a rigorous operator‑algebraic framework for context‑dependent inference, with modular compatibility ensuring consistency between subjective time and learning updates.
· Introduced the Maakoul constant as a quantitative measure of non‑commutative advantage, proving its equality with the Grothendieck constant for bipartite systems and relating it to graph topology.
