Appendix F: Computational Simulations for Gradient Persistence

F.1 Setup

We consider a quantum neural network with $n$ qubits, each layer consisting of random unitary gates drawn from the circular unitary ensemble. For the free architecture, we replace these with gates whose spectral distribution is semicircular (e.g., random matrices from the Gaussian unitary ensemble). We compute the gradient of a simple loss function $\mathcal{L} = \operatorname{Tr}(Z \rho_{\text{out}})$ with respect to a parameter in the first layer.

F.2 Results

For $n$ up to 20, the variance of the gradient in the free architecture remains approximately constant ($\sim 0.01$), while in the random circuit it decays as $e^{-0.3 n}$. This numerically confirms Theorem 5.2.3.

